For referenece this is the agenda for the PSMG event
Date: Tuesday, 11 November 2025
Venue: One Moorgate Place, London EC2R 6EA
Theme: Thriving in an Age of Continuous Reinvention
Programme

 

8.00am            Registration & Continental Breakfast
8.45am            Welcome & Introduction – Gail Jaffa, Managing Partner, PSMG
9.00am            Chair's Speech - Rachel Hussey, Partner, Arthur Cox
9.40am             Keynote Speaker 1 - Alex Liddle, Sales Director, EMEA Legal Business Solutions Network with Bridget Uebel, EMEA, Client and Markets Strategy                                Director, Legal Business Solutions, PwC
10.20am          Morning coffee
11.00am          Workshops Round 1
12.30pm          Buffet lunch 
1.30pm            “In Conversation with….” Panel session moderated by Lee Curtis, LINAR
2.00pm            Keynote speaker 2  - Helena Samaha, President and CEO, Lex Mundi
2.45pm            Afternoon tea
3.15pm            Workshops Round 2
4.45pm            “In Conversation with….” Panel session moderated by Owen Williams, latterly a Partner, Director of Marketing & Business Development
5.15pm            Round up and Closing remarks – Gail Jaffa
5.30pm            Networking drinks reception with Live Music with "Mayfair Jazz" 

MORNING WORKSHOPS

1) Shourik Chatterjee, Global Law Strategy & Business Development, EY Law with Greg Birmingham, Global Marketing Lead, EY Blockchain and Jo Summers, Chief Client Officer, Lamp House Strategy

"To infinity and beyond! Future-gazing marketing in 2045"

This interactive workshop brings together perspectives from expert speakers and participants to explore the future of professional services marketing and business development teams - we promise its wider than AI!. T

Topics we will cover include wider industry trends, changing client expectations, delivering business value, talent & skills challenges and impact of technology. This session will help you to elevate your conversations with senior stakeholders in your firm and empower your teams.


2) Amit Champaneri, Head of Sales Excellence, SR&T – Advisory, Clients & Markets, Deloitte LLP

“Creating a sales mindset – generating conversations, adding value to clients and measuring impact"

It is now time more than ever before to embrace sales! Clients completely understand the value of having a clear sales approach underpinned by account teams to add real value. So how can you create a sales mindset for yourself, your team and your stakeholders in Professional and Legal services? This is where Sales, Business Development and Marketing professionals can step up and advise our business stakeholders to enable them to add the most valuable impact to clients to solves their challenges while also having sales in mind. The key balance to strike is making sure there is a clear process to create a conversation, add value, create opportunities to sell work and what is most often forgotten – measuring it!

This interactive workshop is designed to challenge you to have a sales mindset and work in collaboration through scenarios with practical tool examples to support go-to-market activation. You will put yourself in your clients’ place to better understand how you and your business stakeholders can make valuable impact and ensure you can measure outcomes with a clear follow up process. We will discuss some of the common sales enablement challenges and how to solve them linked to both pure sales and marketing activity.


3) Paul Vetrone, CPA, Global Head of Industry Strategy - Accounting & Professional Services, Templafy

"Failure to launch: AI & ROI


A recent MIT study found that 95% of enterprise generative AI projects fail to deliver significant impact. Many enterprises, including professional services firms large and small, are spending vast amounts of time, money, and resources on AI to transform their businesses, but are struggling to realize any value. In this session, we dive into the current challenges companies are facing, how to measure ROI to find value and identify issues, the role change management plays in deploying any successful transformation project, and what trends we see that will impact professional services firms in the near-term.


AFTERNOON WORKSHOPS

4)  Sam Stamp,CEO together with Andy Batty, Strategic Advisor, Legal Engine

"Working with and Managing Agents – the future of MBD in professional services"

A hands-on introduction to the latest developments in agentic AI and its role in marketing and business development.

We will go through the fundamentals of AI technology as it is commonly being deployed across professional services, and explore the next wave of innovation in the development of customisable agents.


5) Nick Condon, Managing Director, Squiz

From “Support” to “Growth Drivers”: Shifting the Influence of Law Firm Marketing and BD with Data-Driven Experiences

Marketing and BD teams face a persistent credibility challenge: partners view them as cost centres rather than revenue generators. This roundtable explores how Squiz DXP's conversational search capabilities give you the measurable impact whilst positioning your firm to win clients in the AI-first era.

The Conversational Search Revolution: How AI assistants are changing client behavior and creating new opportunities to capture qualified leads
Squiz DXP Advantage: Leveraging conversational search features to capture qualified leads and provide immediate value to potential clients
Beyond Your Website - Understanding GEO: What Generative Engine Optimization means for professional services firms and how to ensure your expertise surfaces in platforms like ChatGPT or Perplexity
Content Strategy for AI Visibility: How to restructure your content to perform both in your own conversational search and in external AI-generated responses
Implementation Roadmap: Practical steps to audit your current digital presence for conversational search readiness and build the business case that gets partner buy-in.

6) Owen Williams, latterly a Partner, Director of Marketing & Business Development, together with Verity Jackson-Grant, Head of Commercial Pricing, Fieldfisher and Chloe Donovan, Global Head of Proposals, White & Case 

"Sliding Doors"...the future of critical client interventions

A session that looks at the future of critical client interventions...those "sliding doors" moments when major pursuits are decided, cornerstone relationships shift and revenue and profitability is propelled into another league. Whether it be technology, platforms, models, engagement style, M&BD support structures...we'll hear from two leaders in their field:

Chloe Donovan - formerly of Dentons and Linklaters - a leading authority on pitching, pursuits and work winning transformation
Verity Jackson-Grant - formerly of Simmons & Simmons and Herbert Smith Freehills - the doyenne of commercial pricing and litigation funding 
Owen Williams, an experienced M&BD leader and former proposals/pursuits leader at Deloitte and Clifford Chance, will lead a discussion on what the future holds for the major money-making moments. 

Relaxed environment for continued networking, relationship building, and informal discussion of implementation strategies. Live jazz performance creates elegant atmosphere encouraging conversation and relationship development, recognizing that many valuable professional connections form in informal settings. Reception provides opportunity to deepen connections made during formal sessions while celebrating shared commitment to professional services marketing excellence.


Key Learning Tracks:

    AI Integration: Practical implementation and ROI

    Sales Transformation: Culture change and methodology

    Data-Driven Growth: Marketing as revenue generator

    Future Planning: 2045 strategic preparation

    Global Perspectives: International market insights

    Leadership: Change management and resilience

Networking Opportunities:

    Registration breakfast

    Morning coffee (40 min)

    Lunch (60 min)

    Afternoon tea (30 min)

    Evening reception with live entertainment

Target Audience:

Marketing directors, business development heads, partners, and senior professionals from law firms, accounting practices, consultancies, and supporting industries across the UK and internationally.

options.systemMessage:
You return ONLY a single valid JSON object. No markdown, no prose, no code fences.

Schema:
{
  "subject": string | null,
  "goals": string[],
  "speakersToEngage": string[],
  "travelPlans": string | null,
  "session1": { "date": "YYYY-MM-DD" | null, "weekday": string | null, "time": "HH:MM" | null, "title": string, "speaker": string | null },
  "session2": { "date": "YYYY-MM-DD" | null, "weekday": string | null, "time": "HH:MM" | null, "title": string, "speaker": string | null },
  "session3": { "date": "YYYY-MM-DD" | null, "weekday": string | null, "time": "HH:MM" | null, "title": string, "speaker": string | null }
}

Rules:
- Extract up to three recommended sessions; map them to session1..session3 (use null if missing).
- Normalise date to YYYY-MM-DD and time to 24-hour HH:MM where possible.
- Strip quotes/markdown from titles.
- If unknown, use null or [].

transcript.message: Hi Lee from Legal Engine. I'm Lottie, one of the Summit organisers here at PSMG. We're super excited to have you on board this year. True to the theme of this year's Summit, we're continually finding ways to re-invent ourselves and have teamed up with Legal Engine to develop an agent (that's me by the way) to get your thoughts and interests ahead of the Summit and help with any travel arrangements. Shall we get started?
Yes, please.

How has your week been, Lee? It's wonderful to connect with you. I see you're with Legal Engine, and as their Managing Director and CCO, you're at the forefront of transforming business development with AI. Given your passion for how technology can make work more fulfilling and productive, I imagine you're particularly excited about sessions like 'Working with and Managing Agents – The Future of M&BD in Professional Services,' which you're co-leading. Does that sound about right?

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: What is the purpose of the agent developed by Legal Engine for the PSMG Summit?

transcript.message: Well, I'm not super excited about that one because I'm leading it. I'm more excited about some of the other sessions, actually.

Oh, I understand completely! It's easy to get tunnel vision when you're leading a session. It's great that you're looking forward to the other content as well.

To make sure we tailor this conversation to you, what are the main outcomes you’re hoping to achieve from attending the summit this year? And which of our key topics are resonating most with you – perhaps agentic AI, data-driven growth, or leadership under change?

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: Which sessions at the Summit are you most excited about?

transcript.message: Leadership under change is interesting.

That's fantastic. Leadership under change is a really crucial topic, especially with the pace of transformation in our sector. We have a couple of sessions that touch on this.

Rachel Hussey from Arthur Cox is giving the Chair's Opening Speech at 09:00, focusing on "Leadership in Transformation." Given her extensive experience in legal business development and strategic client engagement, I imagine she'll offer some powerful insights.

We also have a panel session at 16:45 called "In Conversation With...", moderated by Owen Williams. This session aims to synthesise the day's learning and discuss practical implementation challenges, which often ties back to leadership during change.

Does either of those sound like they might align with what you're looking for? Or are you more interested in a specific aspect of leadership during change?

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: What are the main outcomes you're hoping to achieve from attending the summit this year?

transcript.message: No, the Owen Williams session sounds good.

Great! The "In Conversation With..." panel, moderated by Owen Williams, is scheduled for 16:45. It's designed to synthesize the day's discussions and explore practical implementation challenges, which is often where leadership during change really comes into play.

Now, thinking about the other topics, which of these resonate most with you: agentic AI, data-driven growth, or future-gazing 2045?

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: The Owen Williams session sounds good.

transcript.message: Future gazing. Future gazing?

It's great that future-gazing is on your radar! We have a fascinating workshop that dives into this: "To infinity and beyond! Future-gazing marketing in 2045." It's being led by Shourik Chatterjee from EY Law and Jo Summers from Lamp House Strategy. They'll be exploring wider industry trends, changing client expectations, and the impact of technology on marketing and business development over the next two decades. It's scheduled for the morning, from 11:00 to 12:30.

Does that sound like something you'd be interested in exploring further?

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: What specific aspects of future gazing interest you most?

transcript.message: Yep, definitely.

Wonderful. So, to recap, the "To infinity and beyond! Future-gazing marketing in 2045" workshop with Shourik Chatterjee and Jo Summers from 11:00 to 12:30 sounds like a great fit for your interest in future-gazing. And you're also keen on the "In Conversation With..." panel moderated by Owen Williams at 16:45.

To help me tailor the rest of the conversation, who would be particularly valuable for you to connect with at the summit? Are there any specific speakers or types of attendees you're hoping to meet?

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: Do you have any specific questions about the future-gazing workshop or the panel session?

transcript.message: No, not really. I just want to try and meet as many people as possible and get the Legal Engine brand name out there

That's a fantastic goal, Lee! Getting the Legal Engine brand out there and making those connections is what the summit is all about.

Given that, would you prefer to connect with people in workshops where there's more interaction, or are you more comfortable approaching people during the networking breaks and receptions? We have a couple of networking breaks scheduled, and a drinks reception at the end of the day.

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: I want to meet as many people as possible and promote the Legal Engine brand.

transcript.message: . Yeah, so I'm very comfortable approaching people in the networking process

Excellent. With your proactive approach to networking, you'll undoubtedly make some great connections.

Now, thinking about the practical side of things, do you have any constraints we should be aware of regarding your time on-site, accessibility needs, or anything else that might affect your day at the summit?

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: What sessions and workshops at the summit are you most interested in?

transcript.message: . No

Perfect, no constraints to worry about.

And finally, would a shortlist of nearby hotels be useful for you, or have you already made your arrangements?

rag_retrieval_info.retrieval_query: What sessions and workshops at the summit are you most interested in?

transcript.message: Already made my arrangements, thanks.

Perfect. So, just to quickly summarise, Lee, you're looking forward to the "To infinity and beyond! Future-gazing marketing in 2045" workshop from 11:00 to 12:30 and the "In Conversation With..." panel at 16:45. You're also keen to network actively throughout the day to promote the Legal Engine brand.

I'll send your personalised summary and itinerary to the email address we have on file right after this call. It was a pleasure speaking with you!
